---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Backend | Go (net/http, html/template) |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |
| AI | DeepSeek (via OpenRouter API) |
| Auth | JWT (golang-jwt) + bcrypt |
| Frontend | Tailwind CSS, vanilla JS |
| DevOps | Docker, Docker Compose |

---

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.21+
- Docker & Docker Compose

### Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/V-SemYo/horror-facts.git
cd horror-facts
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — add your OpenRouter API key and JWT secret
docker-compose up -d
go run main.go
Open http://localhost:8080 — enter the void.

Environment Variables
Variable	Description	Default
DB_HOST	PostgreSQL host	127.0.0.1
DB_PORT	PostgreSQL port	5433
DB_USER	Database user	horror
DB_PASSWORD	Database password	—
DB_NAME	Database name	horror_facts
SERVER_PORT	HTTP server port	8080
JWT_SECRET	Secret key for JWT tokens	—
OPENROUTER_API_KEY	API key for AI search	—


Project Structure
text
horror_facts/
├── main.go
├── handlers/
├── templates/
├── static/
├── internal/
│   ├── config/
│   ├── database/
│   ├── repository/
│   ├── middleware/
│   ├── models/
│   └── ai/
├── migrations/
└── data/


API Endpoints
Method	Path	Description	Auth
GET	/	Home page	No
GET	/search?q=	Search movie	No
GET	/movies	All movies archive	No
GET	/filter?category=	Filter by category	No
GET	/map	Horror locations map	No
GET	/login	Login page	No
POST	/login	Login (returns JWT)	No
GET	/register	Registration page	No
POST	/register	Register new user	No
GET	/logout	Logout (clears cookie)	No


About the AI Search
When a user searches for a movie not found in the database, the application sends a request to DeepSeek (via OpenRouter) with the full list of 65 movies as context. The AI returns a structured JSON response matching the database format, which is then rendered using the same template.

text
User query → Search in DB → Not found → DeepSeek API → Parse JSON → Render template
Russian Horror Map
The /map page features a custom world map with pulsing markers for real locations:

Moscow — Kotelnicheskaya Embankment

Oymyakon — Coldest place in Russia

Chernobyl — Exclusion zone legends

Lake Baikal — Sunken NKVD ships

Amityville, NY — 112 Ocean Avenue

Plainfield, WI — Ed Gein's farmhouse

And many more...

